1. Different agencies have varying responsibilities and operational needs, necessitating different levels of funding.
2. Some agencies may be deemed more critical to national security, economic stability, or public welfare, justifying higher budgets.
3. Political priorities and agendas often influence the allocation of budgetary resources, favoring certain agencies over others.
4. Agencies with larger scopes of work or more complex missions typically require greater financial support to fulfill their mandates effectively.
5. Performance and efficiency metrics of agencies can lead to increased budget allocations for those demonstrating better outcomes.